      From the manufacturer

      LUXURIOUS FROM EVERY ANGLE

      Rest Easy, Sit Pretty

      With this mid-century inspired beauty, the design possibilities are endless. Built to provide long-lasting comfort, the Benton combines naturally strong framework and supportive foam cushioning with show stopping details like elegant grid tufting and tapered legs.

      EXPERTLY ENGINEERED

      Take a Supportive Seat

      In sofas as in life, it’s what’s on the inside that counts. Supportive, dense foam cushioning is filled with CertiPUR-US certified foam that meets strict standards for content, emissions and durability. And a naturally strong frame is made to support years of serious couching, but lightweight enough for the bi-annual living room reshuffling.

      A Color Match for Every Style

      ASSEMBLY THAT'S NO SWEAT

      Tool & Headache Free

      That's right, this simple to assemble sofa comes together in just four easy steps. Tools required? Your own two hands, plus the help of a willing friend to maneuver this two seater into the perfect spot. With setup this easy, you'll be unwinding on your new loveseat in less time than it takes to choose your Friday night movie.

          The Benton Sofa may be inspired by the mid-century, but we’re confident that it can bring your living area or family room’s ambiance up to date. To make this handsome piece work with your existing decor, you only need to be a fan of timeless touches, like its versatile color selection, charming grid tufting and organically curved arms. Built sturdy with dense foam and spring cushions, it features medium-firm seating that can comfortably accommodate three people (or maybe just you if it’s time for that afternoon catnap). What could make this purchase even more simple, you ask? An included one-year worry-free warranty and an assembly time that clocks in under 20 minutes. We like to think of it as confident style, all in one box.

          Practical Design and Comfort, finally meet!
          Never thought I would buy a couch online, but clearly I did and here's my input: * Four payment option available from Amazon. No interest/hidden fees. * Color just as expected based on pictures. * Assembly is extremely easy! No special tools (or ANY tools for that matter) are needed. The only screwing involved are the legs to the base. * All pieces (armrests, base and backrest) are "align and snap in". * The comfort is sturdy/firm. I'm 5'10 and can sit comfortably with back all the way to backrest. If you're shorter pillows may be needed so your legs don't stick out, but bend down 45 degree. * If you are accustomed to soft, sink-in kind of sofas, this may not be for you. * Took a nap on it the other day and was quite comfortable. I could see myself sleeping on it whenever my bed needs to be surrendered to visitor. HEADS-UP: * If you live in a walk-up building, or even elevator one, ensure help is available as Amazon driver will NOT deliver to your door. * I specified this under "special instructions to driver", but he just left it in lobby. Box is huge and cumbersome to handle by oneself, which I ended up doing. * I also ended opening the box out in the hallway, taking each piece out and into my apartment one by one. Fortunately each piece is very light (even once put together, the whole sofa is very light, easing the cleaning process. Overall - I give five stars to sofa/designer/maker/. But to amazon deliver service, I give three stars.

          • TheCuriosity
            5.0 out of 5 stars This couch is just what I needed
            Reviewed in Canada on January 31, 2020
            Color: Stone GreySize: SofaPattern Name: Poly LinenVerified Purchase
            Received the couch on Jan 20. Posting this review on Jan 31.

            I really needed a couch. I was living off a terrible futon excuse for a couch and it was killing my humanity.

            I looked at "real" couches, but after measuring my entrance, I sadly came to the conclusion that my entrance can only fit an item of a width of 30 inches and a depth of 33 inches, that I could never have couch that was per-built.

            Then comes in Zinus! I had already purchased a bed frame about two years earlier that I am still very still very content with, so when I saw they also did couches that came in boxes, I was pretty confident in my choice.

            THE PLAYERS: me:: 5 feet 5 inches, 34 inch legs. Partner: 6 feet 0 inches

            GETTING THE COUCH: They just left it on my porch. (no surprise here as that is what they do for everything.) It was big enough that no porch thieves could steal it, but compact enough that if you really wanted to bring it in all by yourself.. it is possible. I wouldn't recommend it. It ideally needs two people to bring it in, but being compact in a box made it easy to do so. My partner did essentially all the work, I just made sure it didn't get stuck on a step. Took all of maybe 2 minutes to get up the stairs and around our weird corner into our apartment.

            PUTTING IT TOGETHER: You will see posts saying that is took them 12 minutes, 10 minutes or what ever, to put it together. For us....well for my partner that insisted on putting it together by himself. It took him a total of (I totally timed it due to seeing if the other reviews were correct) 17 minutes. Mind you.. he put it together wrong TWICE. It wasn't until the second time that he looked at the instructions.. and really.. you don't need to even look at the instructions unless something isn't working right. Once he figured out the right way, it took only 3 minutes of the whole 17 minutes that he took. I feel that it is pretty intuitive to put together.. but if you have a stubborn person around the images help. I believe that opening the box to couch could easily be less than 10 minutes with the right person.

            FIRST IMPRESSIONS: Honestly, the pictures do not do if justice. It looks tight! In a perfect world, I would have had three movable cushions and a darker colour, but, nah.. this really looks great. Impressive, even.

            THE FEEL: When you first sit on it, it may feel "firm" That is a good thing. My partner has been spending hours and hour sitting on it and he is completely find. I have sciatica and this couch is a breath of fresh air. Both of us have tested it twice (or more) with a night of sleep and it is still great. I was initially worried with the 'staying' of cat imprints (noted in one of my pics) but they go away. I mean, obviously it isn't the best foam, but considering the abuse we have pushed on it, it is super comfy. Firm, yes, but perfect for lounging all day long.

            THE SIZE: My 6 foot partner is ecstatic at the height for his legs, for it is actually comfortable for him. For me, at 5'5", it allow a perfect "bend".. I don't know what else to call it, but I can sit perfectly and promote great posture, which helps my sciatica. I feel so great on this couch that even with my sciatica, I feel comfortable in crossing my legs one it and leaning to the side armchair etc; there is just so much support. Speaking of which..

            THE FOAM INSIDE: I included a picture with me pointing out where my cat stepped. "Oh no! There is a dent!!" I thought at first. I now don't really care as the foam of the couch comes back just fine. It probably isn't the best foam insides, but, again, me and my partner have spent ridiculous time on this couch ( I was super sick when it showed up so I didn't leave it for 3 days; when I wasn't there my partner has been sitting on it playing video games.) It handled him, me and my back very well.. So well that I actually ordered something for my bed about two weeks in of owning this couch as I really liked how comfy it was and it made me realize how bad my bed was.

            It is "firm" when you sit.. I guess? But it is a GOOD firm. A comfy firm. A firm you can sit on for hours and play games without issues. It is a great sleep too. Being 5'5", I can stretch out and sleep. With my partner, there is still plenty of room to lie down with him at one end and be comfortable. It is really a great length.

            THE CATS: I have two cats and they immediately demanded a fort, so I made one for them (the were not impressed with me taking a photo.) For the back of the couch, it is a tad thin, but both my 10 pound cat and my 16 pound cat have been able to figure out how to lie comfortably on the back of the couch behind us.

            OVERALL: It isn't a colour I would like, but it is a couch that I could actually fit to get in my apartment. It was easy to put together and it is super comfortable. I love it. I really do.

            UPDATE: Nov 26, 2023... still no regrets. Still comfortable. Amazing for naps too.

            PUTTING IT TOGETHER: You will see posts saying that is took them 12 minutes, 10 minutes or what ever, to put it together. For us....well for my partner that insisted on putting it together by himself. It took him a total of (I totally timed it due to seeing if the other reviews were correct) 17 minutes. Mind you.. he put it together wrong TWICE. It wasn't until the second time that he looked at the instructions.. and really.. you don't need to even look at the instructions unless something isn't working right. Once he figured out the right way, it took only 3 minutes of the whole 17 minutes that he took. I feel that it is pretty intuitive to put together.. but if you have a stubborn person around the images help. I believe that opening the box to couch could easily be less than 10 minutes with the right person.

            FIRST IMPRESSIONS: Honestly, the pictures do not do if justice. It looks tight! In a perfect world, I would have had three movable cushions and a darker colour, but, nah.. this really looks great. Impressive, even.

            THE FEEL: When you first sit on it, it may feel "firm" That is a good thing. My partner has been spending hours and hour sitting on it and he is completely find. I have sciatica and this couch is a breath of fresh air. Both of us have tested it twice (or more) with a night of sleep and it is still great. I was initially worried with the 'staying' of cat imprints (noted in one of my pics) but they go away. I mean, obviously it isn't the best foam, but considering the abuse we have pushed on it, it is super comfy. Firm, yes, but perfect for lounging all day long.

            THE SIZE: My 6 foot partner is ecstatic at the height for his legs, for it is actually comfortable for him. For me, at 5'5", it allow a perfect "bend".. I don't know what else to call it, but I can sit perfectly and promote great posture, which helps my sciatica. I feel so great on this couch that even with my sciatica, I feel comfortable in crossing my legs one it and leaning to the side armchair etc; there is just so much support. Speaking of which..

            THE FOAM INSIDE: I included a picture with me pointing out where my cat stepped. "Oh no! There is a dent!!" I thought at first. I now don't really care as the foam of the couch comes back just fine. It probably isn't the best foam insides, but, again, me and my partner have spent ridiculous time on this couch ( I was super sick when it showed up so I didn't leave it for 3 days; when I wasn't there my partner has been sitting on it playing video games.) It handled him, me and my back very well.. So well that I actually ordered something for my bed about two weeks in of owning this couch as I really liked how comfy it was and it made me realize how bad my bed was.

            It is "firm" when you sit.. I guess? But it is a GOOD firm. A comfy firm. A firm you can sit on for hours and play games without issues. It is a great sleep too. Being 5'5", I can stretch out and sleep. With my partner, there is still plenty of room to lie down with him at one end and be comfortable. It is really a great length.

            THE CATS: I have two cats and they immediately demanded a fort, so I made one for them (the were not impressed with me taking a photo.) For the back of the couch, it is a tad thin, but both my 10 pound cat and my 16 pound cat have been able to figure out how to lie comfortably on the back of the couch behind us.

            OVERALL: It isn't a colour I would like, but it is a couch that I could actually fit to get in my apartment. It was easy to put together and it is super comfortable. I love it. I really do.

            UPDATE: Nov 26, 2023... still no regrets. Still comfortable. Amazing for naps too.
